subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Specimens of this species are represented by two colour 
types
, green (from sites OS11-29, 80; 
Table 1
) and white (sites OS11-9, 11). As there are no obvious morphological differences in carapace shape and chaetotaxy, or size between the two 
types
, we conclude they are conspecific. Differences in the colour of specimens may be related to environmental factors, and similar colour variations have been recorded in other species (e.g. 

Dolerocypris ikeyai
Smith & Kamiya, 2006

; 
Smith 2011
).
